A Finn preparing a work on the Russian hunting traditions and
customs, comes to Russia to collect materials and is invited to take
part in a hunting party. His flamboyant companions include an Army
general, with more than a passing resemblance to Aleksander Lebed, a
police detective, local forest ranger (a devotee of Zen Buddhism) and
some big-city types from St. Petersburg. Inevitably, their good
intentions soon give way to endless drinking, visits to local farm
girls and much else besides.
